article.headline: Hofstra 76, ETSU 75
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Charles Jenkins scored 31 points, including a game-clinching free throw, to lift Hofstra to a 76-75 victory over East Tennessee State on Sunday in the Charleston Classic. ETSU relinquished a 75-71 lead in the final 2:39. With the score tied at 75, Hofstra (2-1) had the ball and called timeout with 17.7 seconds to play. The Pride inbounded to Jenkins, who milked the clock before driving the lane and drawing a foul with 1.1 seconds remaining. Jenkins made the first free throw, then missed the second shot hard off the backboard. Mike Smith cleared the rebound for ETSU (1-2), but his desperation heave toward the basket was off the mark. Smith led the Buccaneers with 20 points. For the Pride, Cornelius Vines scored all 16 of his points in the first half before aggravating a thumb injury
